---
description: Delete unused variables instead of prefixing with underscore
alwaysApply: true
---

# No Underscore Hacks for Unused Variables

When a destructured property or variable is unused, DELETE it.
Do NOT rename it with an underscore prefix.

```typescript
// BAD — underscore cruft
const { token, user: _user } = data

// GOOD — just don't destructure it
const { token } = data
```

The `_` prefix is ONLY acceptable for:

- Callback parameters required by a signature where you
  need a later positional arg (e.g. `(_req, res)`)
- Intentionally ignored iterator variables
  (e.g. `Array.from({ length: 3 }, (_, i) => i)`)

If neither of those applies, remove the declaration.
